rComments: He's a nice person but not a very good prof. So difficult to pay attention to him that a lot of people stopped showing up to his lectures and just read the textbook and did their best. The material itself isn't difficult he's just so hard to focus on.
teacherRatingTags: ['Caring', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Pros: - If you like condensed notes, you'll find them useful but that also means there's a lot to unpack. - does a decent job at helping students during his office hours. - Gave extensions to deadlines Cons: - Rarely respond to emails - Occasionally answers questions on the feeble discussion board on Quercus (IMO, Piazza is effective)

Lectures aren't mandatory because his lecture notes are clear and concise, but he often goes into further clarification in class if the topic is a bit tricky. His assignments are a bit hard, but he'll lead you on the right track if you feel confused. His midterm and final were very fair. He's kind and chill, definitely a prof to look forward to!

His lectures are easy to follow, and although he makes up for any small mistakes and seems a little nervous throughout his lectures, you can't help but admire his likable and friendly nature. He's a very nice professor and is always willing to provide tons of help and gives very fair tests and assignments that test the main concepts from class.

As a lecturer, he is pretty difficult to pay attention to. He makes up for it by making his notes very high quality, enough that they were enough to learn everything in the course. Also if you visit him during office hours, he will give you tons of help, and he will explain everything you did wrong on your assignment/exams.
